#Text=[0886] Example 14a, Step f: A solution of crude ((7R,8S)-8-Amino-1,4-dioxa--spiro[4.5]dec-7-yl)-methanol (0.086 mol) in 300 mL of CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 was treated with a 120 mL of saturated Na.sub.2CO.sub.3, and cooled in an ice bath.
#Text=The mixture was stirred vigorously while benzyl chloroformate (17.3 mL, 0.108 mol) was added slowly.
#Text=After the addition was complete the mixture was stirred for an additional 30 min.
#Text=The organic layer was separated and washed with water, brine and concentrated to give 33 g of crude product.
#Text=This was recrystallized from hexane to give pure Benzyl (1S,2R)-2-(hydroxymethyl)-4-(1,3-dioxolane)cyclohexylcarbamate.
#Text=[0887] .sup.1H NMR (300 MHz, CDCl.sub.3) .delta.
#Text=(TMS):

#Text=[0888] Example 14a, Step 1: Benzyl (1S,2R)-2-(hydroxymethyl)-4-(1,3-dioxol-ane)cyclohexylcarbamate was dissolved in dry CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 prior to the addition of triethylamine (9.4 mL) This solution was cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. and methanesulfonyl chloride (3.4 mL) was added.
#Text=The resulting solution was stirred 2 h before saturated sodium bicarbonate was added.
#Text=The organic layer was separated and the aqueous layer re-extracted with CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2.
#Text=The combined organic layer was washed with brine and dried (Na.sub.2SO.sub.4).
#Text=It was then filtered, concentrated and dried in vacuo to get (1R,2S)-2-(benzyloxycarbonyl)-5-(1,3-dioxolane)-cyclohexyl)m-ethyl methanesulfonate as a pale yellow oil.
#Text=It was used without any further purification.
#Text=[0889] Example 14a, Step 2: To a solution of isopropanethiol (6.3 ml, 67.72 mMol) in anhydrous DMF at 0.degree.
#Text=C. was added sodium hydride (2.7 g, 67.72 mMol) in small portions under a nitrogen flush.

#Text=After the effervescence subsided, the cooling was removed and stirring continued at rt for 90 min after which ((1R,2S)-2-(benzyloxycarbonyl)-5-(1,3-dioxolane-)-cyclohexyl)methylmethane sulfonate(33.86 mMol) was dissolved in DMF (50 mL) and added slowly to the reaction.
#Text=After 4 h, saturated NH.sub.4Cl was added to the reaction.
#Text=Partitioned between ethyl acetate and water.
#Text=Aqueous layer was re-extracted with ethyl acetate.

#Text=The combined organic layer was washed with brine and dried (MgSO.sub.4) After filteration and concentration, a flash column yielded benzyl (1S,2R)-2-(isopropylthiometh-yl)-4-(1,3-dioxolane)cyclohexyl carbamate as a pale oil (8.16 gm, 63% yield over two steps).

#Text=[0890] Example 14a, Step 3: A sample of benzyl (1S,2R)-2-(isopropylthiomet-hyl)-4-(1,3-dioxolane)cyclohexyl carbamate (8.15 g) was dissolved in acetonitrile (50 mL) prior to the addition of 1N HCl (50 mL).
#Text=After 30 h the reaction was made basic by portionwise addition of saturated NaHCO.sub.3.
#Text=It was then partitioned between EtOAc and water.
#Text=The aqueous layer was re-extracted with EtOAc.
#Text=The combined organic layer was washed with brine and dried (MgSO.sub.4).
#Text=Filtered, concentrated and dried in vacuo to result in benzyl (1S,2R)-2-(isopropylthiomethyl)-4-oxocyclohexyl-carbamate as a clear oil (6.57 g, quant. yield).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=336.1.
